But in 1993 a Zambian Air Force ditches into the ocean about 500 metres offshore from Gabon. All passengers, including 18 players, die in the accident.The Chipolopolo's captain, Kalusha Bwalya, who is not aboard the ill-fated flight puts his efforts to build a new team and make a professional federation becoming later the national team coach and president of the Football Association of Zambia. programme.title: Made in Senegal
programme.desc: Made in Senegal is a story about will, dreams, determination, faith, rebellion, courage and love. The film invites us on a journey through Sadio´s different and highly diverse worlds - from the rural life in a small village in the far south of Senegal to the spotlight of world football by playing for Liverpool FC, even winning the Champions Leagues as number 10 with the world watching… The interaction of animations, documentary scenes, a diverse set of in-depth interviews and archive footage brings Sadio´s past to life and creates an exciting and emotional plot.

programme.title: Everyday Spartans: Episode 1
programme.desc: Joe De Sena – Spartan Founder and Team Leader welcomes the team to Japan where they must climb iconic Mt. Fuji. As their first challenge, they scale the Atago stairs, a Samurai-honored tradition with a kettlebell for company. If that’s not enough, De Sena makes them run around the famed Imperial Palace. However, this time around there is a surprise for them from Rakuten. What other surprises are around the corner?

programme.title: Everyday Spartans: Episode 2
programme.desc: The Spartans are all set to climb Mt.Fuji a challenge that not only requires physical prowess but tremendous mental strength. A Japanese monk helps the Spartans cleanse their minds by guiding them through the time-tested practice of taking on the full force of an icy-cold waterfall – an experience they will never forget. As they undertake their arduous climb, their egos and frayed nerves begin to get in the way of staying together as a team. The shared responsibility of lugging along a 45-kg accessory certainly does not help their cause. Will they come together before it’s too late?

programme.title: Everyday Spartans: Episode 3
programme.desc: While the team begins to come together as one, awareness dawns on how different their individual attitudes and confidence levels are. While one of them, realizes they cannot complete the task and prepares to descend, another questions if her pace is setting everyone back. Keeping her on and walking at her pace would mean sacrificing watching the prized sunrise at the summit. Are they ready to give up on that ? They are getting beaten down, but they must go on. Will they make it before sunrise?

programme.title: Everyday Spartans: Episode 4
programme.desc: A sea of clouds and a magical sunrise await the team at the summit. With the team’s belief in themselves and each other reinforced, they think about what it took to overcome their obstacles. The moment is especially poignant for one member who pays tribute to the memory of his late son and spends a quiet moment in remembrance of him. As each of them grapple with the emotions that overtake them on the summit, Joe De Sena reminds them that reaching the summit is not the end of their journey – its’s only the beginning. Where will the Spartan spirit take them next?

programme.title: Everyday Spartans: Episode 5
programme.desc: After an extraordinary adventure in Japan, the Spartans head to America . De Sena is not pleased with the baggage they are carrying– lateness, injuries and poor body maintenance. Will an extended dip in an icy lake shake their reverie? Under the guidance of a survival expert, they must climb a massive rock as one unit with only a rope holding them all together. Every member must think every step through for the sake of the team. For, one miscalculated step could very well lead to disaster. Can they handle the heat of this challenge?

programme.title: The Secrets of La Roja – World Champions 2010
programme.desc: On the 11th July 2010, Spain’s national team reached its goal of winning the World Cup, a victory that was felt by the team and nation as a whole. Despite this successful ending, “La Roja” had to overcome various struggles and difficulties in order to become legendary. The team arrived in South Africa with the triumph of the 2008 European Football Championship under their belt and Vicente del Bosque leading the way. There was a general feeling of favoritism attributed to ""La Roja"" and while the defeat against Switzerland in the first match came as a shock, it motivated Del Bosque and his team to come together and focus on one intention: good football and one goal: to make history.

programme.title: MessiCirque

We will accompany the creators, artists and Messi on a trip from Montreal to Barcelona and discover a story about dreams that come true. MessiCirque combines Cirque du Soleil´s vision to tell, for the first time, the story of a living sports legend with a child´s ambition to play football.

programme.title: SEVE - Artist, Fighter, Legend

This is his story, from members of his inner circle, other sporting greats and from himself via newly unearthed material.

programme.title: Last Days In The Desert
programme.desc: Suffused with mystery, and set against breath-taking landscapes, this bold and dramatic interpretation of the temptations of Christ explores Jesus’ confrontation with the devil in his last days fasting Judean desert. Finally contemplating a return to civilisation, and his imminent death, Jesus happens upon a troubled family dealing with a much more earthly problem: the young son being desperate to leave the familial home against his father’s wishes, in search of the big city. Amid this family struggle we see Jesus wrestling not only with Satan, but also with his own faith.

programme.title: The Face of Love
programme.desc: Five years after the death of her beloved husband Garrett (Ed Harris), Nikki (Annette Bening) meets Tom, a man who who looks exactly like her deceased husband. Not only does Tom possess the same physical characteristics, but he also shares Garrett's kindness, humour, and passion for art. Suddenly, a flood of old feelings rush back to Nikki: she's met the love of her life. Again.

programme.title: 5 to 7
programme.desc: An aspiring novelist enters into a relationship with a woman, though there's just one catch: She's married, and the couple can only meet between the hours of 5 and 7 each evening.

programme.title: Finding Altamira
programme.desc: 1879, nine-year-old Maria Sautuola and her father, Marcelino, discover the first cave art and accomplished paintings of galloping bison. But Maria's mother, devout Conchita, is disturbed at the idea that prehistoric savages could have created such magnificent art. The Catholic Church sees this as an attack on Biblical truth. And Carthailac, the leading prehistorian, condemns Marcelino and his discovery as fakes. The family is thrown into crisis and the cave locked up. It takes all their love for each other to find a way through to redemption and recognition.

programme.title: Black Mountain
programme.desc: At a site 100 miles from the nearest native reservation, during a Canadian winter, a group of archaeologists have made a startling discovery: The tip of a mysterious, ancient structure, which bears some archaic engravings. The crew, led by Jensen, attempt to decipher it but some mysteries are better left buried. As they delve further into the structure's origins, things at their camp turn strange. Communications fail, local workers suddenly disappear and the men are stricken with a terrible illness. It's not long before they begin to feel the effects of solitude and then things get really bad...

programme.title: Guardians of the Tomb
programme.desc: An innocent discovery of a well-preserved mummified Emperor unearths a 2000-year-old nightmare - a secret that should have remained buried. A team of scientists, who lose a colleague in an ancient labyrinth, must work together to recover him while trying to make the discovery of a century. In their quest to rescue him, they find themselves underground, battling ancient, terrifying Chinese magic and making their way through a swarm of deadly, man-eating spiders – only to uncover the secret behind the insects’ power and intelligence.

programme.title: 16 Blocks
programme.desc: They chose the worst man for the job. They expected him to fail, but he wasn't about to let a witness be murdered on his watch. Personal demons put Jack (Bruce Willis - Die Hard, Anti-Life) a New York City cop at rock bottom. But when he's assigned to escort a petty criminal to testify before the grand jury, a violent turn of events means this down-and-out cop needs to pull it together to save not only the life of the witness but his own as they are hunted across the city. The clock is ticking in this exhilarating race against time. Will justice be served or will there be two more bodies to add to the crime toll of the city?

programme.title: Invasion Planet Earth
programme.desc: After the death of his young daughter, Tom Dunn is a broken man. When his wife falls pregnant again, he cannot believe their luck. However, his joy is short-lived, as, on the very same day, the people of Earth become plagued with terrifying visions of the end of the world. When a gigantic, all-consuming alien mothership appears in the sky and launches a ruthless attack on Earth's cities, chaos and destruction follow. Tom must find the strength and wisdom to save his wife and unborn child. However, first he must confront a shocking truth. A truth which threatens the key to the survival of the human race. The ultimate war for Planet Earth is about to begin...

programme.title: Adventurer: The Curse of the Midas Box
programme.desc: Seventeen-year-old Mariah Mundi’s life is turned upside down when his younger brother is kidnapped from the streets of Victorian London. Following a trail of clues to the darkly majestic Prince Regent Hotel, Mariah discovers a hidden realm of child-stealing monsters, sinister strangers, deadly secrets and a long-lost artifact that grants limitless wealth – but also devastating supernatural power. With the fate of his world, and his family at stake, Mariah will risk everything to unravel the Curse of the Midas Box!

programme.title: Mortdecai
programme.desc: Juggling some angry Russians, the British Mi5, his impossibly leggy wife and an international terrorist, debonair art dealer and part time rogue Charlie Mortdecai (Johnny Depp) must traverse the globe armed only with his good looks and special charm in a race to recover a stolen painting rumored to contain the code to a lost bank account filled with Nazi gold.

programme.title: Kill Command
programme.desc: Set in the very near future, an elite squad of highly trained marines, led by commanding officer Captain Bukes, are sent on a routine training exercise to a remote island, from which all communications have been cut off. Accompanying them on the mission is 'tech head' Specialist Mills, a mysterious coder whose brain is interfaced with a computer. When they reach the island, the unit soon discover they are not alone and the exercise is far from routine. They become live targets of terrifyingly advanced military robots and begin to suspect that Mills is somehow involved in the conspiracy. But without the help of Mill's technology, they know they won't survive.
